title: Negotiations for a New Cabinet
subtitle: The *formateur* is to form a new cabinet.
new-page: true
tags: event
max-visits: 1
view-if: natsir_vonc = 1 and bpp_join != 1
face-image: img/portraits/sartono.jpg
go-to: natsir_demands

= Negotiations for a New Cabinet

In attempting to establish a cabinet based on the <span style="color: #990000;">**PNI**</span> and the <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span>, Sartono encountered various difficulties. The two parties are entrenched to opposing stands to matters of the turnover tax, regional councils based on Regulation 39, the distribution of seats, and the complex problems surrounding the West Irian Issue and Indonesian-Dutch relations. On the last series of matters in particular both parties are most divided from one another, with the <span style="color: #990000;">**PNI**</span> wanting a unilateral abrogation of the Netherlands-Indonesia Union and other parts of the Round Table Conference, while the <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span> insisting all cancelations of agreements must be made in bilateral accord.

But the most prominent of matters is the Prime Ministership. Sartono pressed the <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span> to accept Susanto Tirtoprodjo of the <span style="color: #990000;">**PNI**</span> and governor of the Lesser Sunda Islands as Prime Minister. On the other hand, the <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span> argued that because this new cabinet will follow the general policy which had been set forth and implemented by the Natsir cabinet, Natsir himself should again be the Prime Minister.

Nevertheless, negotiations have begun. The <span style="color: #000000;">**Masjumi**</span> has presented their demands.

